titleStmt.title: Istanbul, Topkapı Palace Museum (Topkapı Sarayı Müzesi), "Saray Medina 1b" (Gotthelf Bergsträßer archives) [= Karatay 2]

msIdentifier.repository: Topkapı Palace Museum (Topkapı Sarayı Müzesi) , Istanbul

summary.p: 134 fol. (Karatay: 135 fol.); Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: M. 3; Text: Q 9:6- Q 32:22; 14 lines per page; Dimensions: 140 x 175 mm (according to Karatay 1962: 260 x 355 mm); Script style: kūfī, type C.III; Estimated date of production: 700-900 (?), [1st (7th) to 2nd (8th) centuries according to Karatay 1962]. G. Bergsträßer lists this manuscript as of Medinan provenance without precise information. The catalogue entry in Karatay 1962 does not mention Medina as provenance of this fragment.

This entry is based on the catalogue of Fehmi E. Karatay (1888-1968) and black-and-white images from the archives of Gotthelf Bergsträßer refering to the manuscript as "Istanbul, Saray, Medina 1b" (unfortunately, the images of the recto sides of fol. 20-57 and fol. 62r are not available). This manuscript is mentioned also in the 3rd volume of the Geschichte des Qorans (by Gotthelf Bergsträßer, published after his death by Otto Pretzl) where "Tafel III" gives an image with the caption "Istanbul, Saray, Medina 1b, ca. 14x 17,5 cm, Sure 21, 39-45". The catalogue of Arabic manuscripts of the Topkapı-Sarayı-Museum, written by Karatay mentions a fragment "M.3" which has the same part of the Qurʾānic text (Q 9:6 until Q 32:22) and the same number of lines to the page as "Istanbul, Saray, Medina 1b". Bergsträßer gives as dimensions "ca. 14x 17,5 cm", different from those in Karatay's catalogue: 260 x 355 mm. Most probably, "Istanbul, Saray, Medina 1b" (Bergsträßer) corresponds to call number "M. 3" (Karatay) even if Karatay mentions 133 fol., instead of 134 fol. (Bergsträßer).

The entry Topkapı Sarayı catalogue has the following information, Fehmi Ethem Karatay, Topkapı Sarayı Müzesi Kütüphanesi Arapça Yazmalar Kataloǧu, Istanbul 1962, p. 1: "M 3 muṣḥaf, Parşömen. 260mm boy ve 355mm eninde cönk şeklinde 133 yaprak. Sahifede kûfî yazı ile 290mm. uzunl. 14 satır. Tahminen I-II (VII-VIII) asırda yazılmıştır. Sure başları kırmızı, nefhi, sarı ve sepya ile hendesi ve geçmeli tezyinatı havidir, Miklep ve şemseli koyu zeytunî deri cilt. Bu mushaf Tavba (9) suresinin 70. ayetinin اتهم رسلهم بالبينات cümlesiyle başlayıp Sacda (32) suresinin 22. ayeti ومن اظلم kelimesiyle bitiyor."

Esra Gözeler and Tuba Karaşahin have translated Karatay's catalogue entry as follows: "Parchment. 133 oblong/horizontally shaped folia of 260 mm length and 355 mm width. The text, written in Kufic script [contains] 14 lines measuring 290 mm. Probably copied during the 1st and 2nd (7th and 8th) centuries. Sūra incipit contains red, dark green, yellow, and sepia geometric and interlaced painted decorations. Dark olive-coloured leather binding with flap (miklep) and a mandorla (şemse). The codex begins with اتتهم رسلهم بالبينات of Q 9:70 (Sūra al-Tawba) and ends with the words ومن اظلم of Q 32:22 (Sūra al-Sajda)."
